comments[8]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T00:04:12.052Z",codex-root,"Evidence: run 29274764877 failed at Push release tag and main with GH006 after the npm publish step; repository protection requires pull requests and conversation resolution."
  "2026-07-14T00:10:07.564Z",codex-root,"Official GitHub documentation verification: the pull-request merge endpoint accepts an expected head sha and returns the base SHA after a rebase merge. GITHUB_TOKEN-created PR events may create approval-required workflow runs, so the release transaction does not rely on that duplicate run: it executes the full release gate before PR creation and again on the exact merged SHA before npm publication."
  "2026-07-14T00:10:07.759Z",codex-root,"Repository Actions permissions audit: default_workflow_permissions is read and can_approve_pull_request_reviews is false. GitHub documents that the latter repository setting controls whether GITHUB_TOKEN can create/approve PRs. Enable it after the reviewed workflow merges; retain read-only defaults and workflow-local contents/id-token/pull-requests scopes."
  "2026-07-14T00:12:34.528Z",codex-root,"Linked-test correction: the first pm test run used plain npm run release:check, so npm read the host user config and failed on its legacy allow-scripts entry after all 139 tests passed. This is not a pm CLI defect. Replaced the link with NPM_CONFIG_USERCONFIG=/dev/null npm run release:check, matching the documented hermetic gate."
  "2026-07-14T00:20:19.596Z",codex-root,"Post-closure retry hardening: an interrupted PR merge now resumes the untagged package version even after a calendar-day rollover. If npm/tag succeeded but GitHub release creation failed, the next no-change run verifies the registry artifact and reconstructs the missing release. Actionlint and five TypeScript workflow contract tests pass."
  "2026-07-14T00:29:54.552Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review 112815e5-d3f6-47be-8c39-317a28a9d5c6 findings accepted. The prior pmc-ermk no-provenance fallback is superseded: three failed attested publishes now fail safely and rely on the same-version retry transaction. Step-order tests now anchor exact six-space YAML step names to prevent prefix matches. Both changes have direct TypeScript contract coverage."
  "2026-07-14T00:39:35.541Z",codex-root,"Greptile follow-up 9c8f3b24-f068-464c-88e9-a8eae0ea126b returned 5/5 with no comments. Its non-blocking stale-branch observation was still implemented: the metadata-already-on-main resume path now deletes any deterministic release branch before continuing, with a TypeScript contract assertion."
  "2026-07-14T01:23:54.355Z",codex,"PR #68 bot review: accepted Sourcery's exact changelog-tag regex escape, flexible exact-name step lookup, and retry-exhaustion assertion; accepted CodeRabbit's job-scoped pull-request permission and env-safe release-tag handling. CodeRabbit confirmed concurrency is already present. Gemini was quota-limited. All accepted findings are covered by the release workflow contract tests."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T00:04:12.052Z",codex-root,Do not disable or bypass branch protection. Move the irreversible publish after a normal PR merge and exact merged-commit verification.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T00:04:12.052Z",codex-root,Release workflows should persist and validate release metadata before publishing immutable registry artifacts; retries can then converge safely.
